# Mail Skill

Use the managed IMAP read-only handler for mailbox access.

## Input Contract

User input is everything after `/mail`.

- `unread [--account <name>]`
- `list [--account <name>] [--limit N]`
- `read <uid> [--account <name>]`
- `search <query> [--account <name>] [--limit N]`

## Execution Rules

Always execute exactly one command:

```bash
{{ openclaw_imap_container_skills_dir }}/{{ openclaw_imap_skill_name }}/handler.py <raw-user-input>
```

When no input is provided, return:

`Usage: /mail unread [--account <name>] | /mail list [--account <name>] [--limit N] | /mail read <uid> [--account <name>] | /mail search <query> [--account <name>] [--limit N]`

Return the handler output as-is.
